{# module-docs.tera: Renders rustdoc module-level documentation for a SourceModule ontology instance. #}
{# Constitutional Equation: //! block in src/<moduleName>.rs = mu(wasm4pm-compat.ttl, SourceModule) #}
{# Input variables: #}
{#   moduleName           — snake_case module name, e.g. "ocel" #}
{#   rustType             — primary public Rust type, e.g. "OcelLog" #}
{#   description          — one-paragraph description of what this module is #}
{#   processForm          — process-model family this module represents, e.g. "ObjectCentricEventLog" #}
{#   paperReference       — citeKey or DOI for the defining paper #}
{#   graduatesToWasm4pm   — boolean #}
{#   laws                 — array of law names this module must satisfy #}
{# Output: //! doc comment block, ready to paste at the top of src/<moduleName>.rs #}
{# Auto-generated by ggen from wasm4pm-compat.ttl --- DO NOT EDIT #}
//! # `{{ moduleName }}` — {{ rustType }}
//!
//! {{ description }}
//!
//! ## What this module IS
//!
//! The canonical structure-only representation of [`{{ rustType }}`] in the
//! `wasm4pm-compat` crate. This module defines the **shape** of
//! `{{ processForm }}` evidence — every field, every link, every identifier
//! type — exactly as the boundary law requires.
//!
//! All types here are **zero-engine**: they hold data but never discover,
//! replay, align, or check conformance. That is an engine concern belonging
//! in `wasm4pm`.
//!
//! ## What this module is NOT
//!
//! - **Not** a parser. External bytes become [`crate::state::Raw`] evidence
//!   first; admission is the only lawful Raw → Admitted path.
//! - **Not** a validator. Shape validity is enforced by the type system and
//!   by [`crate::admission::Admit`] implementations; this module does not
//!   run checks at construction time.
//! - **Not** a discovery or conformance engine. No process-mining algorithms
//!   belong here.
{% if paperReference %}
//!
//! ## Defining authority
//!
//! This module implements the structure described in `{{ paperReference }}`.
//! The corresponding witness type is used to tag every piece of evidence
//! admitted against this authority.
{% endif %}
{% if laws | length > 0 %}
//!
//! ## Laws this module satisfies
//!
{% for law in laws %}
//! - `{{ law }}`
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% if graduatesToWasm4pm %}
//!
//! ## Graduation
//!
//! Types in this module **graduate to `wasm4pm`**. When a caller needs to
//! actually verify or execute against `{{ processForm }}` — not merely hold
//! its structure — the value travels into the `wasm4pm` engine via
//! [`crate::graduation::GraduateToWasm4pm`]. Structure-only use stays here.
{% else %}
//!
//! ## Graduation
//!
//! Types in this module are **structure-only** and do not currently graduate
//! to `wasm4pm`. If a consumer needs engine-level operations against
//! `{{ processForm }}`, open a graduation issue and implement
//! [`crate::graduation::GraduateToWasm4pm`].
{% endif %}
//!
//! ## When to use this module
//!
//! Use `{{ moduleName }}` when you need to:
//!
//! - Hold a typed `{{ rustType }}` value in memory after admission.
//! - Construct a `{{ rustType }}` for testing or projection.
//! - Pass a `{{ rustType }}` to a loss-accounting [`crate::loss::Project`] impl.
//! - Export a `{{ rustType }}` via a [`crate::formats`] surface (requires the
//!   `formats` feature).
//!
//! Do **not** use this module to run discovery, conformance checking, replay,
//! or any other process-mining computation. Those graduate to `wasm4pm`.
